<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFF13929EBD2C361FAD35F8D" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF13929EBD2C361FEAA5F5A" blockId="95.[227,341,1106,1132]" box="[227,341,1106,1132]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<heading id="5A24A609FFF13929EBD2C361FEAA5F5A" bold="true" box="[227,341,1106,1132]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929EBD2C361FEAA5F5A" bold="true" box="[227,341,1106,1132]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF13929EBD2C34CFAD35F8D" blockId="95.[227,1436,1151,1211]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
These otoliths seem to show most affinities with those of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF13929E8CBC3B3FBB05FAF" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1816" box="[1018,1103,1152,1177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sparidae" genus="Pagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929E8CBC3B3FBB05FAF" box="[1018,1103,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Pagrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be attributed to that genus (see 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFF13929EA54C393FE1E5F8D" author="Nolf D." box="[357,481,1184,1211]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" refId="ref55873" refString="Nolf D. 2018. Otoliths of Fishes from the North Sea and the English Channel. Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Brussels." type="book" year="2018">Nolf 2018</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 57 for iconography of the Recent 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF13929E8AFC392FAD75F8D" authority="pagrus (Linnaeus, 1758))" authorityName="pagrus (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[926,1320,1184,1211]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sparidae" genus="Pagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pagrus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF13929E8AFC392FBB45F8C" box="[926,1099,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Pagrus pagrus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758))
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
